<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

							*Problematic Internet Use Questionnaire (PIUQ)*
							*with 18 items()
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 12-18-2020
last updated:  02-25-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-25-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

This script implements the Problematic Internet Use Questionnaire (PIUQ) by Demetrovics et al (2008).
The PIUQ was tested with a sample that ranged in age from 12-69 (mean: ~23).

Reference

Demetrovics, Z., Szeredi, B., & Rózsa, S. (2008). The three-factor model of Internet addiction: 
The development of the Problematic Internet Use Questionnaire. Behavior Research Methods, 40, 563-574.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

18 questions, 5-point Likert Scale (never - always)

Subscales
Obsession: Questions 1, 4, 7, 10, 13, 16
Neglect: Questions 2, 5, 8, 11, 14, 17
Control disorder: Questions 3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 1.5 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________		
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'piuq.iqdat'

date, time:							date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  		 with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:								the Inquisit build 

q*_response:						response given (in assigned values)
									Scale: 1 (never) - 5 (always)
									no reversed scored questions
									
q*_latency:							how much time (in ms) the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular 
									question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)


(2) Summary data file: 'piuq_summary.iqdat' (Inquisit Lab: one data file per participant)

inquisit.version:					Inquisit version run
computer.platform:					the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:							date script was run
startTime:							time script was started
subjectid:							assigned subject id number
groupid:							assigned group id number
sessionid:							assigned session id number
elapsedTime:						time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:							0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
									1 = script was completed (all conditions run)
									
numberMissingItems:					the number of questions that have not been answered 
Note: by default settings, all questions are required to be answered. However, that setting can be changed.
If default setting is changed, the above variable can be used as a flag.

//Total and Subscale Scores: scored on scale: 1 (never) to 5 (always)
PIUQ_total:							the total score (range: 18-90); 
PIUQ_Obsession:						the score on subscale 'obsession' (range: 6-30) 
PIUQ_Neglect:						the score on subscale 'neglect' (range: 6-30)  
PIUQ_ControlDisorder:				the score on subscale 'controldisorder' (range: 6-30) 									
+ z-scores and percentiles if applicable
									
+ responses to individual items
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
QUESTIONNAIRE SET-UP & SCORING
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________								

18 questions, 5-point Likert Scale (never - always)

Subscales
Obsession: Questions 1, 4, 7, 10, 13, 16
Neglect: Questions 2, 5, 8, 11, 14, 17
Control Disorder: Questions 3, 6, 9, 12, 15, 18

Scoring:
Each question is scored on a scale 1 (never) to 5 (always)
A subscale score is computed for each of the 3 subscales based on the sum of the individual responses.
The Total PIUQ score is based on the sum of all responses.

Norms are calculated (if gender is provided) by default based on data (means and standard deviations)
provided by Demetrovics et al (2008, p.569, table 7).
Check out section Editable Parameters to turn off the demographic questions (and norm calculations).

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:


</usermanual>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/ calculateGenderNorms = true		//true = the script collects gender information and calculates z-scores and percentiles based on reported gender
									//false = the script does not collect gender information (and does not calculate z-scores/percentiles)
</parameters>

**************************************************************************************************************
				!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0 or higher

<defaults>
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/txbgcolor = white
/ txcolor = black
/ screencolor = white
</defaults>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DATA
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

***********************
summary data file
***********************
<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform,, script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId,script.sessionId, 
script.elapsedTime, script.completed,
values.numberMissingItems,
radiobuttons.gender.response, textbox.age.response,
expressions.PIUQ_total, values.z_score_PIUQ, values.percentile_PIUQ,
expressions.PIUQ_Obsession, values.z_score_O, values.percentile_O, 
expressions.PIUQ_Neglect, values.z_score_N, values.percentile_N,
expressions.PIUQ_ControlDisorder, values.z_score_C, values.percentile_C,
radiobuttons.q1_o.response, radiobuttons.q2_n.response, radiobuttons.q3_c.response, 
radiobuttons.q4_o.response, radiobuttons.q5_n.response, radiobuttons.q6_c.response,
radiobuttons.q7_o.response, radiobuttons.q8_n.response, radiobuttons.q9_c.response, 
radiobuttons.q10_o.response, radiobuttons.q11_n.response, radiobuttons.q12_c.response,
radiobuttons.q13_o.response, radiobuttons.q14_n.response, radiobuttons.q15_c.response,
radiobuttons.q16_o.response, radiobuttons.q17_n.response, radiobuttons.q18_c.response
)
</summarydata>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES: automatically updated
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<values>
/numberMissingItems = 0
</values>

//norming data (see Demetrovics et al, 2008, p.569, table 7)
<values>
/mean_F_O = 9.2
/SD_F_O = 3.9

/mean_F_N = 12.1
/SD_F_N = 4.1

/mean_F_C = 11.3
/SD_F_C = 4.1

/mean_F_Total = 32.6
/SD_F_Total = 10.0

/mean_M_O = 9.1
/SD_M_O = 3.8

/mean_M_N = 13.0
/SD_M_N = 4.4

/mean_M_C = 10.3
/SD_M_C = 3.7

/mean_M_Total = 32.4
/SD_M_Total = 9.7

/z_score_O = "not calculated"
/percentile_O = "not calculated"

/z_score_N = "not calculated"
/percentile_N = "not calculated"

/z_score_C = "not calculated"
/percentile_C = "not calculated"

/z_score_PIUQ = "not calculated"
/percentile_PIUQ = "not calculated"
</values>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	EXPRESSIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<expressions>
/PIUQ_Obsession = radiobuttons.q1_o.response + radiobuttons.q4_o.response + radiobuttons.q7_o.response + 
radiobuttons.q10_o.response + radiobuttons.q13_o.response + radiobuttons.q16_o.response

/PIUQ_Neglect = radiobuttons.q2_n.response + radiobuttons.q5_n.response + radiobuttons.q8_n.response + 
radiobuttons.q11_n.response + radiobuttons.q14_n.response + radiobuttons.q17_n.response

/PIUQ_ControlDisorder = radiobuttons.q3_c.response + radiobuttons.q6_c.response + radiobuttons.q9_c.response +
radiobuttons.q12_c.response + radiobuttons.q15_c.response + radiobuttons.q18_c.response

/PIUQ_Total = expressions.PIUQ_Obsession + expressions.PIUQ_Neglect + expressions.PIUQ_ControlDisorder

/generateGenderNorms = {
	if (radiobuttons.gender.response == "Female"){
		values.z_score_PIUQ = (expressions.PIUQ_Total - values.mean_F_Total)/values.SD_F_Total;
		values.percentile_PIUQ = pofz(values.z_score_PIUQ);
		
		values.z_score_O = (expressions.PIUQ_Obsession - values.mean_F_O)/values.SD_F_O;
		values.percentile_O = pofz(values.z_score_O);

		values.z_score_N = (expressions.PIUQ_Neglect - values.mean_F_N)/values.SD_F_N;
		values.percentile_N = pofz(values.z_score_N);		

		values.z_score_C = (expressions.PIUQ_ControlDisorder - values.mean_F_C)/values.SD_F_C;
		values.percentile_C = pofz(values.z_score_C);	
	} else if (radiobuttons.gender.response == "Male"){
		values.z_score_PIUQ = (expressions.PIUQ_Total - values.mean_M_Total)/values.SD_M_Total;
		values.percentile_PIUQ = pofz(values.z_score_PIUQ);
		
		values.z_score_O = (expressions.PIUQ_Obsession - values.mean_M_O)/values.SD_M_O;
		values.percentile_O = pofz(values.z_score_O);

		values.z_score_N = (expressions.PIUQ_Neglect - values.mean_M_N)/values.SD_M_N;
		values.percentile_N = pofz(values.z_score_N);		

		values.z_score_C = (expressions.PIUQ_ControlDisorder - values.mean_M_C)/values.SD_M_C;
		values.percentile_C = pofz(values.z_score_C);	
	}	 	
}
</expressions>


*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false

<radiobuttons q1_o>
/caption = "1. How often do you fantasize about the Internet, or think about what it would be like to be online when you are not on the Internet?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q2_n>
/caption = "2. How often do you neglect household chores to spend more time online?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q3_c>
/caption = "3. How often do you feel that you should decrease the amount of time spent online?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q4_o>
/caption = "4. How often do you daydream about the Internet?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q5_n>
/caption = "5. How often do you spend time online when you’d rather sleep?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q6_c>
/caption = "6. How often does it happen to you that you wish to decrease the amount of time spent online but you do not succeed?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q7_o>
/caption = "7. How often do you feel tense, irritated, or stressed if you cannot use the Internet for as long as you want to?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q8_n>
/caption = "8. How often do you choose the Internet rather than being with your partner?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q9_c>
/caption = "9. How often do you try to conceal the amount of time spent online?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q10_o>
/caption = "10. How often do you feel tense, irritated, or stressed if you cannot use the Internet for several days?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q11_n>
/caption = "11. How often does the use of Internet impair your work or your efficacy?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q12_c>
/caption = "12. How often do you feel that your Internet usage causes problems for you?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q13_o>
/caption = "13. How often does it happen to you that you feel depressed, moody, or nervous when you are not on the Internet and these feelings stop once you are back online?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q14_n>
/caption = "14. How often do people in your life complain about spending too much time online?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q15_c>
/caption = "15. How often do you realize saying when you are online, “just a couple of more minutes and I will stop”?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q16_o>
/caption = "16. How often do you dream about the Internet?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q17_n>
/caption = "17. How often do you choose the Internet rather than going out with somebody to have some fun?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons q18_c>
/caption = "18. How often do you think that you should ask for help in relation to your Internet use?"
/ options = ("Never", "Rarely", "Sometimes", "Often", "Always")
/ optionvalues = ("1", "2", "3", "4", "5")
/required = true
/orientation = horizontalequal
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons gender>
/ caption = "What is your gender?"
/ options = ("Female", "Male", "Other", "I prefer not to answer")
/ required = true
</radiobuttons>

<textbox age>
/ caption = "What is your age?"
/ mask = positiveintegerorzero
/ required = false
</textbox>

<caption end>
/ caption = "- END OF QUESTIONNAIRE -"
/ position = (45%, 93%)
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2%, false, true, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = gray
</caption>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage piuq_1>
/ caption ="In the following you will read statements about your Internet use. Please indicate how much these statements characterize you.
"
/ questions = [1 = q1_o, q2_n, q3_c]
</surveypage>

<surveypage piuq_2>
/ caption ="In the following you will read statements about your Internet use. Please indicate how much these statements characterize you.
"
/ questions = [1 = q4_o, q5_n, q6_c]
</surveypage>

<surveypage piuq_3>
/ caption ="In the following you will read statements about your Internet use. Please indicate how much these statements characterize you.
"
/ questions = [1 = q7_o, q8_n, q9_c]
</surveypage>

<surveypage piuq_4>
/ caption ="In the following you will read statements about your Internet use. Please indicate how much these statements characterize you.
"
/ questions = [1 = q10_o, q11_n, q12_c]
</surveypage>

<surveypage piuq_5>
/ caption ="In the following you will read statements about your Internet use. Please indicate how much these statements characterize you.
"
/ questions = [1 = q13_o, q14_n, q15_c]
</surveypage>


<surveypage piuq_6>
/ caption ="In the following you will read statements about your Internet use. Please indicate how much these statements characterize you.
"
/ questions = [1 = q16_o, q17_n, q18_c]
</surveypage>

<surveypage piuq_demographics>
/ caption = "Please answer the following questions."

/ skip = [
	parameters.calculateGenderNorms == false;
]
/ questions = [1 = age, gender, end]
</surveypage>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEY
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Notes:
- presents the surveypages
- to take pictures of each screen set /screencapture = true

<survey piuq>
/pages = [
	1 = piuq_1;
	2 = piuq_2;
	3 = piuq_3;
	4 = piuq_4;
	5 = piuq_5;
	6 = piuq_6;
	7 = piuq_demographics;
]
/screencapture = false
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, true, false, false, 5, 1)
/ subcaptionfontstyle = ("Arial", 2%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ itemfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, true, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 2.5%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = (0, 0, 0)
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ showquestionnumbers = false
/ navigationbuttonfontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (15%, 5%)
/ backbuttonposition = (20%, 90%)
/ nextbuttonposition = (70%, 90%)
/ navigationbuttonsize = (20%, 5%)
/ finishlabel = "Submit"
/ onblockend = [
	if (radiobuttons.q1_o.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}
	if (radiobuttons.q2_n.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q3_c.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q4_o.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q5_n.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q6_c.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q7_o.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q8_n.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q9_c.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q10_o.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q11_n.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}
	if (radiobuttons.q12_c.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q13_o.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q14_n.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q15_c.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q16_o.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q17_n.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	if (radiobuttons.q18_c.response == ""){
		values.numberMissingItems += 1;
	}	
	
	expressions.generateGenderNorms;
]
</survey>

